# Third-Party Licenses

<!-- markdownlint-disable -->

This file is **auto-generated** by [`cargo-about`](https://github.com/EmbarkStudios/cargo-about)
from `Cargo.lock` + `about.toml`, covering every third-party Rust crate in the `mycelium` workspace
dependency graph (first-party `mycelium-*` crates and the private `xtask` tool are excluded — they
are covered by the repo-root `LICENSE`, MIT, per ADR-022 §7). It exists to preserve the
attribution/notice terms (MIT/BSD/ISC "include this copyright notice", Apache-2.0 §4(d) NOTICE,
etc.) that third-party permissive licenses require when the workspace's binaries/artifacts ship.

**Regenerate:** `just licenses` (wraps `cargo about generate about.hbs -o THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md`).
**Do not hand-edit** — update `about.toml` (accepted-license set) or `about.hbs` (this template)
instead, then regenerate. `cargo-deny` (`deny.toml`) is the enforcement gate for which licenses are
*allowed* in the tree; this file is the notice-preservation record for what's actually in it — the
two should stay in lockstep (a license accepted here but not in `deny.toml`'s `allow` list, or vice
versa, is a drift signal, not expected steady state).

**Scope note (never-silent, G2):** this file covers the **Rust** dependency graph only. The
optional Python `gpu` dependency-group under `experiments/` (`uv sync --group gpu`) pulls
NVIDIA-proprietary CUDA runtime packages under NVIDIA's own EULA — not OSI-approved, not covered by
this file, opt-in only, and never part of a distributed Mycelium artifact. See
`experiments/README.md` for the full disclosure.

